reviews.text: Amazing little restaurant tucked away on the second floor of one of the newly renovated buildings at the Old Police Station and Prison Museum. You can come early and grab a drink at the bar below on the first floor. This is a Thai restaurant with great food. A very nice and sometimes spicy array of food that is served in shareable plates of food. Nice wine selection. There is indoor and outdoor seating. I suggest reservations as this place can get busy.

Thai restaurant by David Thompson, located in the old Police HQ in HK. 

Service was amazing. Couldn't do enough on the night and were totally engaged from the time I walked in. 

The menu isn't the standard Thai fare which makes Aaharn even more interesting for me. 

My red curry Pork main was seriously spicey but incredibly delicious. 

Will go back for sure.
Delicious and beautifully presented Thai food by David Thompson. Lots of interesting flavours and texture. Wished some of the dishes could be spicier . Great selection with the tasting menu.
Very mediocre, won't be coming back again. Portion size is small with a big price tag. Flavours are mediocre, some dishes were too salty.

This restaurant is on the second floor in the former police headquarters building. Stylish and hip decor gave me a good first impression. There was a choice of inside or balcony seating. The menu includes a 7 course set meal and a la cart items. We chose the set meal. Every course was good. We particularly liked the salad, fried fish, and taro dessert. We got the soup a la cart. It's very spicy but we loved it. We got there when it wasn't busy. The staff was friendly and very attentive. This place is now my favorite Thai in this area.
